description: Numbers n whose prime factors are 2 and 7.
comments: n such that phi(n)=(3/7)*n - _Benoit Cloitre_, Apr 19 2002A143201(a(n)) = 6; subsequence of A143204. [_Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011]
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
prog: (Haskell)import Data.Set (singleton, deleteFindMin, insert)a033847 n = a033847_list !! (n-1)a033847_list = f (singleton (2*7)) where   f s = m : f (insert (2*m) $ insert (7*m) s') where     (m,s') = deleteFindMin s-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011
